f64::<impl f64>::abs.doc:
Computes the absolute value of `self`.

This function always returns the precise result.

# Examples

```
let x = 3.5_f64;
let y = -3.5_f64;

assert_eq!(x.abs(), x);
assert_eq!(y.abs(), -y);

assert!(f64::NAN.abs().is_nan());
```

